olive oil
1 capsicum
1 carrot
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 white turnip
1 packet pork mince
½ packet panko breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
3 clove garlic
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 tsp honey
1 leek
1 bag parsley

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut capsicum, carrot and white
turnip into bite-sized chunks. Thickly slice white and light green parts of
leek.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with
garlic & herb seasoning. Toss to coat. Spread out evenly, then roast until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

• While the veggies are roasting, finely chop garlic.
• In a large bowl combine pork mince, garlic, panko breadcrumbs (see ingredients), the egg, chicken-style stock powder and the salt. Using damp hands, form heaped spoonfuls of pork mixture into meatballs, then flatten to make 2cm-thick rissoles. Transfer to a plate. You should get 3-4 rissoles per person.

• When the veggies have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook rissoles in batches until browned and cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat. Add the honey, tossing rissoles to coat.

• Divide herby roasted veggies between plates. Top with pork rissoles.
• Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese. Tear over parsley leaves.
Spoon over dill & parsley mayonnaise to serve.